cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on proposing novel inference schemes and demonstrating their applications in computer vision, specifically in generative and discriminative vision models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes new neural network architectures, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves graph-based message-passing inference, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
